cs.AR, cs.EM, cs.SY, cs.PF, cs.ET 

Reasoning: 
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture): The paper focuses on evaluating the energy consumption of embedded processors, which falls under the domain of hardware architecture. 
- cs.EM (Embedded Systems): The benchmark suite is targeted at evaluating energy consumption on embedded platforms, which is a key aspect of embedded systems. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper discusses the properties of the benchmark suite and how it can be used to evaluate energy consumption on different hardware platforms, which falls under the domain of systems and control. 
- cs.PF (Performance): The paper evaluates the performance of different processor architectures in terms of energy consumption, which falls under the domain of performance evaluation. 
- cs.ET (Emerging Technologies): The paper discusses the use of the Adapteva Epiphany processor, which is a relatively new and emerging technology in the field of embedded systems.
